oduction to the theory and, specifically, the practice of Cognitive Linguistics and by trajectories for further reading that start out from the individual chapters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCognitive grammar. 4aCognitive Linguistics. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCognitive linguistics.  alinguistic theorie.1 aBrugman, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColston, Herbert L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCroft, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFauconnier, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFillmore, Charles J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeeraerts, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeeraerts, Dirk, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGibbs, Jr., Raymond W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldberg, Adele E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLakoff, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangacker, Ronald W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTalmy, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomasello, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuggy, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA 